    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Richard Petrow was an American author.  Much of his writing focused on some aspect of marine stewardship, including shrimping, boating, arctic seas, and oil spills.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Richard Petrow Papers</emph> consists of correspondence and 
		writings.  The majority of the collection is research notes for his book 
		<emph render="italic">The Black Tide</emph>, which deals with the 1967 wreck of the 
		tanker <emph render="italic">Torrey Canyon</emph> and the ensuing oil spill on the 
		coasts of Cornwall (England) and Brittany (France).  </p>
		
		<p>The collection begins with a small amount of <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>.  
		<emph render="bold">Writings</emph> includes notes, galleys, proofs, and research material 
		relating to articles, books, and scripts written by Petrow.  The majority concerns <emph render="italic">The Black Tide</emph>, but there is also material from his book <emph render="italic">Across the Top of Russia</emph>, about the cruise of the U.S. Coast Guard ship <emph render="italic">Northwind</emph> into the polar seas north of Siberia.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Correspondence is arranged alphabetically by correspondent.   Writings are arranged alphabetically by type and within that by title of work.</p>
    </arrangement>
